# Drag-and-drop for lists and tables

## Default — flat and simple lists

Whenever the renderer needs **drag-and-drop to reorder items in a list** (for example **`QList`** / **`QItem`**, vertical settings rows, chip lists, or any non-tree, non-**`QTable`** collection), use **[`vue-draggable-plus`](https://vue-draggable-plus.pages.dev/en/)** (`package.json` dependency).

- Prefer **`VueDraggable`** with **`v-model`** on the backing array, or **`useDraggable`** / **`v-draggable`** when the list root is not a plain wrapper (for example Quasar list bodies).
- Use a dedicated **drag handle** (grip icon on **`QItemSection`**) via Sortable **`handle`** when rows also navigate or open menus on click.
- Persist new order through existing Pinia + IPC patterns after drop; map indices to domain fields (for example **`sort_order`** on worlds).
- **Vertical tab strips** (for example **Project Settings** world / document-template tabs): **`vue-draggable-plus`** with **`src/scripts/faDragDrop/`** (**`buildFaVerticalDraggableTabsRootStyle`**, sortable options, drag cursor) and **`faVerticalDraggableTabs`** SCSS. TabList hosts expose layout props (**`tabListWidthPx`**, **`tabPadding`**, **`tabTextAlign`**, **`tabJustifyContent`**, **`tabLabelTextTransform`**, **`tabLabelFontSize`**, **`dense`**) — see **`types/I_faVerticalDraggableTabs.ts`** and [fantasia-drag-drop skill](../skills/fantasia-drag-drop/SKILL.md) **Vertical draggable tab strips**.

**Do not** add SortableJS, **`vuedraggable`**, **`vue-draggable-next`**, or ad hoc HTML5 **`draggable`** for list reorder unless a maintainer documents a narrow exception in review.

## Exception 1 — hierarchical trees (`@he-tree/vue`)

When the UI is a **nested expand/collapse tree**, use **`@he-tree/vue`** (`BaseTree` / **`Draggable`**) and its **built-in drag-and-drop**. **Do not** wrap tree nodes with **`vue-draggable-plus`** or replace he-tree DnD.

See [fa-he-tree.mdc](fa-he-tree.mdc) and [fantasia-he-tree skill](../skills/fantasia-he-tree/SKILL.md).

## Exception 2 — **`QTable`** row reorder

When reordering **rows inside a Quasar `QTable`**, use **`quasar-ui-q-draggable-table`** (**`v-draggable-table`** directive). The app registers it from boot file **`src/boot/q-draggable-table.ts`**.

- Set directive **`options.mode`** to **`'row'`** for row reorder (default column mode is for column drag).
- Implement **`onDrop(from, to)`** to splice the backing **`rows`** array; the library reports indexes only — it does not mutate Vue state.
- **Row mode is incompatible with `virtual-scroll`** on the same table; use a non-virtual table or another UX for very large row sets.
- Column reorder uses the same directive with **`mode: 'column'`** when that product need arises.

**Do not** use **`vue-draggable-plus`** on **`QTable`** body rows.

## Out of scope (custom pointer sessions)

**Spatial** drag (movable floating windows, free-position panels) stays in feature **`src/scripts/`** pointer sessions (for example **`faFloatingWindowTitleDragPointerSession`**) — not list libraries above.

